cards.Body_Text: Don't Insult My Intelligence: Whenever one of your characters challenges another character, gain 1 lore.

cards.Name: Tigger - One Of A Kind
cards.Flavor_Text: Bouncing in to save the day!
cards.Body_Text: Energetic: Whenever you play an action, this character gets +2 {s} this turn.

cards.Name: Tuk Tuk - Wrecking Ball
cards.Flavor_Text: A good friend is always ready to roll.
cards.Body_Text: Reckless (This character can't quest and must challenge each turn if able.)

cards.Name: Go The Distance
cards.Body_Text:
(A character with cost 2 or more can {e} to sing this song for free.)
Ready chosen damaged character of yours. They can't quest for the rest of this turn. Draw a card.

cards.Name: Teeth and Ambitions
cards.Flavor_Text: Of course, quid pro quo, you're expected To take certain duties on board
cards.Body_Text:
(A character with cost 2 or more can {e} to sing this song for free.)
Deal 2 damage to chosen character of yours to deal 2 damaged to another chosen character.

cards.Name: The Most Diabolical Scheme
cards.Flavor_Text:
Now comes the real tour de force
Tricky and wicked, of course
cards.Body_Text:
(A character with cost 3 or more can {e} to sing this song for free.)
Banish chosen Villain of your to banish chosen character.

cards.Name: What Did You Call Me?
cards.Flavor_Text:
"No one can have a higher opinion of your than I have, and I think you're a slimy, contemptible sewer rat!"
 - Basil
cards.Body_Text: Chosen damaged character gets +3 {s} this turn.

cards.Name: You Can Fly!
cards.Body_Text:
(A character with cost 2 or more can {e} to sing this song for free.)
Chosen character gains Evasive until the start of your next turn. (Only characters with Evasive can challenge them.)

cards.Name: Dinner Bell
cards.Flavor_Text: The delicate sound of impending doom.
cards.Body_Text: You Know What Happens: {e}, 2 {i} - Draw cards equal to the damage on chosen character of yours, then banish them.

cards.Name: Peter Pan's Dagger
cards.Flavor_Text: Like so much other lore, Peter Pan's dagger was safe in the Great Illuminary until the flood.
cards.Body_Text: You characters with Evasive get +1 {s}.

cards.Name: Sword In The Stone
cards.Flavor_Text: "Whoso pulleth out this sword of this stone and anvil is rightwise king born of England."
cards.Body_Text: {e}, 2 {i} - Chosen character gets +1 {s} this turn for each 1 damage on them.

cards.Name: Alice - Growing Girl
cards.Body_Text: Good Advice - Your other characters gain Support. (Whenever they quest, you may add their {s} to another chosen character's {s} this turn.) What Did I Do? - While this character has 10 {s} or more, she gets +4 {l}.

cards.Name: Basil - Great Mouse Detective
cards.Flavor_Text: A solution always presents itself.
cards.Body_Text:
Shift 5 (You may pay 5 {i} to play this on top of one of your characters named Basil.)
There's Always A Chance: If you used Shift to play this character, you may draw 2 cards when he enters play.

cards.Name: Basil - Of Baker Street
cards.Flavor_Text: "What an ingenious device! If its light is refracted through these, then its images must resolve somewhere below."
cards.Body_Text: Support (Whenever this character quests, you may add their {s} to another chosen character's {s} this turn.)

cards.Name: Basil - Perceptive Investigator
cards.Flavor_Text: "There is no question: something is afoot in the Great Illuminary"

cards.Name: Caterpillar - Calm and Collected
cards.Flavor_Text: "Keep your tempo."

cards.Name: Cogsworth - Grandfather Clock
cards.Body_Text:
Shift 3 (You may pay 3 {i} to play this on top of one of your characters named Cogsworth.)
Ward (Opponents can't choose this character except to challenge.)
Unwind: Your other characters gain Resist +1 (Damage dealt to them is reduced by 1)

cards.Name: Cogsworth - Talking Clock
cards.Flavor_Text: "This has gone far enough. I'm in charge here."
cards.Body_Text: Wait A Minute: Your characters with Reckless gain "{e} - Gain 1 lore."

cards.Name: Cruella De Vil - Fashionable Cruiser
cards.Flavor_Text: "Isn't it just gorgeous darling? And just as stylish as I am."
cards.Body_Text: Now Get Going: During your turn, this character gains Evasive. (They can challenge characters with Evasive.)

cards.Name: Cruella De Vil - Perfectly Wretched
cards.Flavor_Text: "It's ink couture, darling. I wear only the best!"
cards.Body_Text:
Shift 3 (You may pay 3 {i} to play this on top of one of your characters named Cruella De Vil.)
Oh, No You Don't: Whenever this character quests, chosen opposing character gets -2 {s} this turn.

cards.Name: Duke Weaselton - Small-Time Crook
cards.Flavor_Text: "It's Wee-sel-ton."
cards.Body_Text: Ward (Opponents can't choose this character except to challenge.)

cards.Name: Gaston - Intellectual Powerhouse
cards.Body_Text:
Shift 4 (You may pay 4 {i} to play this on top of one of your characters named Gaston.)
Developed Brain: When you play this character, look at the top 3 cards of your deck. You may put one into your hand. Put the rest on the bottom of your deck in any order.

cards.Name: Grand Pabbie - Oldest And Wisest
cards.Flavor_Text: When he talks, even the sky listens.
cards.Body_Text: Ancient Insight: Whenever you remove 1 or more damage from one of your characters, gain 2 lore.

cards.Name: Hiram Flaversham - Toymaker
cards.Flavor_Text: His creations are even more wondrous with the Illuminary's resources at his fingertips.
cards.Body_Text: Artificer: When you play this character and whenever he quests, you may banish one of your items to draw 2 cards.

cards.Name: James - Role Model
cards.Body_Text: Never, Ever Lose Sight: When this character is banished, you may put this card into your inkwell facedown and exerted.

cards.Name: Jasmine - Heir Of Agrabah
cards.Flavor_Text: She may be young, but she's got the spirit of a true leader
cards.Body_Text: I'm A Fast Learner: When you play this character, remove up to 1 damage from chosen character of yours.

cards.Name: Judy Hopps - Optimistic Officer
cards.Flavor_Text: "I'll get to the bottom of what happened with that locked lorebook. You can count on me!"
cards.Body_Text: Don't Call Me Cute: When you play this character, you may banish chosen item. Its player draws a card.

cards.Name: Mrs. Judson - Housekeeper
cards.Flavor_Text: "I know just the thing. Let me fetch you a pot of tea and some of my fresh cheese crumpets."
cards.Body_Text: Tidy Up: Whenever you play a Floodborn character, you may put the top card of your deck into your inkwell facedown and exerted.

cards.Name: Nick Wilde - Wily Fox
cards.Flavor_Text: "It's criminal how good these things taste!"
cards.Body_Text: It's Called A Hustle: When play this character, you may return an item card name Pawpsicle from your discard to your hand.

cards.Name: Noi - Orphaned Thief
cards.Body_Text: Hide And Seek: While you have an item in play, this character gains Resist +1 and Ward. (Damage dealt to this character is reduced by 1. Opponents can't choose this character except to challenge.)

cards.Name: Owl - Logical Lecturer
cards.Flavor_Text: "For instance, based on the quality of the light and the subtle change in wind direction, I can safely say that it is time for tea."

cards.Name: Prince Charming - Heir To The Throne
cards.Flavor_Text: He'd searched across the Inklands for the young woman who'd stolen his heart at the ball, only to find more mysteries.

cards.Name: Rabbit - Reluctant Host
cards.Flavor_Text:
Pooh: "Isn't there anybody here at all?"
Rabbit: "Nobody!"
Pooh: "Somebody's there... because somebody must have said 'Nobody.'"

cards.Name: Sisu - Divine Water Dragon
cards.Flavor_Text: No matter her shape, you can't mistake her heart.
cards.Body_Text: I Trust You: Whenever this character quests, look at the top 2 cards of your deck. You may put one into your hand. Put the rest on the bottom of your deck in any order.

cards.Name: The Nokk - Water Spirit
cards.Flavor_Text: As elusive as water.
cards.Body_Text: Ward (Opponents can't choose this character except to challenge.)

cards.Name: Winnie The Pooh - Having A Think
cards.Flavor_Text: When he though, he though in the most thoughtful way he could think.
cards.Body_Text: Hunny Pot: Whenever this character quests, you may put a card from your hand into your inkwell facedown.

cards.Name: Falling Down The Rabbit Hole
cards.Flavor_Text: Down, down, down she went, floating in a swirl of ink. How curious!
cards.Body_Text: Each player chooses one of their characters and puts them into their inkwell facedown and excreted.

cards.Name: Four Dozen Eggs
cards.Body_Text:
(A character with cost 3 or more can {e} to sing this song for free)
Your characters gain Resist +2 until the start of your next turn. (Damage dealt to them is reduced by 2.)

cards.Name: Launch
cards.Flavor_Text: Ready... aim... coconut?
cards.Body_Text: Banish chosen item of yours to deal 5 damage to chosen character.

cards.Name: Nothing To Hide
cards.Flavor_Text: Helps you avoid unpleasant surprises.
cards.Body_Text: Each Opponent reveals their hand. Draw a card.

cards.Name: Fang Crossbow
cards.Body_Text:
Careful Aim: {e}, 2 {i} - Chosen character get -2 {s} this turn.
Stay Back!: {e}, Banish this item - Banish chosen Dragon character.

cards.Name: Gumbo Pot
cards.Flavor_Text:
"A gift this special just got to to be shared."
-James
cards.Body_Text: The Best I've Ever Tasted: {e} - Remove 1 damage each from up to 2 chosen characters.

cards.Name: Maurice's Workshop
cards.Flavor_Text: The solution you need could be just a few adjustments away.
cards.Body_Text: Looking For This: Whenever you play another item, you may pay 1 {i} to draw a card.

cards.Name: Pawpsicle
cards.Body_Text:
Jumbo Pop: When you play this item, you may draw a card.
That's Redwood: Banish this item - Remove up to 2 damage from chosen character.

cards.Name: Sardine Can
cards.Flavor_Text:
"Flight 3759 boarding now! Let's go get that lore!"
-Orville
cards.Body_Text: Flight Cabin: Your exerted characters gain Ward. (Opponents can't choose them except to challenge.)

cards.Name: Beast - Forbidding Recluse
cards.Flavor_Text: Woe to the one who draws his gaze.
cards.Body_Text: You're Not Welcome Here: When you play this character, you may deal 1 damage to chosen character.

cards.Name: Beast - Selfless Protector
cards.Flavor_Text: "You'll have to go through me first."
cards.Body_Text: Shield Another: Whenever one of your other character would be dealt damage, put that many damage counters on this character instead.

cards.Name: Beast - Tragic Hero
cards.Flavor_Text: "It must be my destinyto remain a beast forever."
cards.Body_Text:
Shift 3 (You may pay 3 {i} to play this on top of one of your characters named Beast.)
It's Better This Way: At the start of your turn, if this character has no damage, draw a card. Otherwise, he gets +4 {s} this turn.

cards.Name: Benja - Guardian of the Dragon Gem
cards.Flavor_Text: "Don't mistake spirit for skill."
cards.Body_Text: We Have A Choice: When you play this character, you may banish chosen item.

cards.Name: Chief Bogo - Respected Officer
cards.Flavor_Text: "We can confirm the ink flood was caused by an explosion. We have it under controlnow clear the area."
cards.Body_Text: Insubordination!: Whenever you play a Floodborn character, deal 1 damage to each opposing character.

cards.Name: Cinderella - Knight In Training
cards.Flavor_Text: She's always had the heart of a championnow she'll have the skills, too.
cards.Body_Text: Have Courage: When you play this character, you may draw a card, then choose and discard a card.

cards.Name: Cinderella - Stouthearted
cards.Body_Text: Shift 5 (You may pay 5 {i} to play this on top of one of your characters named Cinderella.) Resist +2 (Damage dealt to this character is reduced by 2.) The Singing Sword: Whenever you play a song, this character may challenge ready characters this turn.

cards.Name: Donald Duck - Deep-Sea Diver
cards.Flavor_Text: "You go ahead, Minnie! I'm going to see if there's any lore over here."

cards.Name: Eli La Bouff - Big Daddy
cards.Flavor_Text: "I don't suppose y'all could whip up some more magical beignets with them inkcasters?"

cards.Name: Goofy - Knight for a Day
cards.Flavor_Text: It's a banner day for Sir Goofy, who is steeled to prove his mettle against anyone courting trouble-jouse in case.

cards.Name: Hercules - Divine Hero
cards.Flavor_Text: A good guy to have around when something wrecks your inkworks.
cards.Body_Text: Shift 4 (You may pay 4 {i} to play this on top of one of your characters named Hercules.)\nResist +2 (Damage dealth to this character is reduced by 2.)

cards.Name: Hercules - Hero In Training
cards.Flavor_Text: No need to call IX-I-I!

cards.Name: Jafar - Dreadnought
cards.Body_Text: Shift 2 (You may pay 2 {i} to play this on top of one of your characters named Jafar.)\nNow Where Were We?: During your turn, whenever this character banishes another character in a challenge, you may draw a card.

cards.Name: Jafar - Royal Vizier
cards.Flavor_Text: "Soon you'll learn who holds the real power!"
cards.Body_Text: I Don't Trust Him, Sire: During your turn, this character gains Evasive. (They can challenge characters with Evasive.)

cards.Name: Kronk - Junior Chipmunk
cards.Body_Text: Resist +1 (Damage dealt to this character is reduced by 1.)\nScout Leader: During your turn, whenever this character banishes another character in a challenge, you may deal 2 damage to chosen character.

cards.Name: Lawrence - Jealous Manservant
cards.Flavor_Text: In this new world, the crown could finally be his.
cards.Body_Text: Payback: While this character has no damage, he gets +4 {s}.

cards.Name: Li Shang - Archery Instructor
cards.Flavor_Text: Learn what to do, then learn to do it without thought.
cards.Body_Text: Archery Lesson: Whenever this character quests, your characters gain Evasive this turn. (They can challenge characters with Evasive.)

cards.Name: Magic Broom - Industrial Model
cards.Flavor_Text: Even with a hauling weight of "seriously, a lot," it can only do so much in a magical flood.
cards.Body_Text: Make It Shine: When you play this character, chosen character gains Resist +1 until the start of your next turn. (Damage dealt to them is reduced by 1.)

cards.Name: Namaari - Morning Mist
cards.Body_Text: Bodyguard (This character may enter play exerted. An opposing character who challenges one of your characters must choose one with Bodyguard if able.)\nBlades: This character can challenge ready characters.

cards.Name: Pacha - Village Leader
cards.Flavor_Text: "Don't be fooled by the folksy peasant look." - Kuzco

cards.Name: Prince Naveen - Penniless Royal
cards.Flavor_Text: All he's got is his charm.

cards.Name: Queen Of Hearts - Capricious Monarch
cards.Flavor_Text: The forth Rule of Villainy: Do whatever it takes to get ahead.
cards.Body_Text: Off With Their Heads!: Whenever an opposing character is banished, you may ready this character.

cards.Name: Robin Hood - Capable Fighter
cards.Flavor_Text: "Capable? You don't know the half of it." - Little John
cards.Body_Text: Skirmish {e} - Deal 1 damage to chosen character.

cards.Name: The Huntsman - Reluctant Enforcer
cards.Flavor_Text: "Run away, hide! In the woods, anywhere!"
cards.Body_Text: Change Of Heart: Whenever this character quests, you may draw a card, then choose and discard a card.

cards.Name: The Prince - Never Gives Up
cards.Body_Text: Bodyguard (This character may enter play exerted. An opposing character who challenges one of your characters must choose one with Bodyguard if able.)\nResist +1 (Damage dealt to this character is reduced by 1.)

cards.Name: Tiana - Celebrating Princess
cards.Body_Text: Resist +2 (Damage dealt to this character is reduced by 2.)\nWhat You Give Is What You Get: While this character is exerted and you have no cards in your hand, opponents can't play actions.

cards.Name: Tiana - Diligent Waitress
cards.Flavor_Text: "My place is going be special, with great food to fill people's bellies and hot jazz to feed their souls!"

cards.Name: Charge!
cards.Flavor_Text: Sometime subtlety is required. This is not one of those times.
cards.Body_Text: Chosen character gains Challenger +2 and Resist +2 this turn. (They get +2 {s} while challenging. Damage dealt to them is reduced by 2.)

cards.Name: Let The Storm Rage On
cards.Flavor_Text: The cold never bothered me anyway
cards.Body_Text: (A character with cost 3 or more can {e} to sing this song for free.)\nDeal 2 damaged to chosen character. Draw a card.

cards.Name: Pick A Fight
cards.Flavor_Text: "I'm gonna wreck it!"
cards.Body_Text: Chosen character can challenge ready characters this turn.

cards.Name: Strength Of A Raging Fire
cards.Flavor_Text: Tranquil as a forest\nBut on fire within
cards.Body_Text: (A character with cost 3 or more can {e} to sing this song for free.) Deal damage to chosen character equal to the number of characters you have in play.

cards.Name: Last Cannon
cards.Flavor_Text: One shot can change everything.
cards.Body_Text: Arm Yourself: 1 {i}, Banish this item - Chosen character gains Challenger +3 this turn. (They get +3 {s} while challenging.)

cards.Name: Mouse Armor
cards.Flavor_Text: Built by the tiniest of hands for the bravest of hearts.
cards.Body_Text: Protection - {e}: Chosen character gains Resist +1 until the start of your next turn. (Damage dealt to them is reduced by 1.)

cards.Name: Weight Set
cards.Flavor_Text: Personally endorsed by Hercules himselff!
cards.Body_Text: Training - Whenever you play a character with 4 {s} or more, you may pay 1 {i} to draw a card.
